                        <h3>Overcoming the "Manual Workflow Trap"</h3>
                        <p><strong>Attendees:</strong> Craig (Superior Security), Harris Tariq, Matthew Beecham.</p>
                        <p style="margin-top: 1rem;">Superior Security NW is ready for the next level, but current tools are reaching their limit. Key pain points identified:</p>
                        <ul>
                            <li><strong>The Google Docs Bottleneck:</strong> Managing 4 in-house lads and 6 subbies across Google Docs and Calendars is becoming unscalable for 3 office staff.</li>
                            <li><strong>Professional Image:</strong> Manual job sheets and scanning are time-consuming and don't match the quality of service provided to major clients like Starbucks and Motor Fuel Group.</li>
                            <li><strong>PPM Management:</strong> Critical need for an automated way to schedule recurring door and shutter services (6-12 month cycles) without manual tracking.</li>
                            <li><strong>Disconnected Finances:</strong> While Xero is used, the lack of a "Set it and Forget it" link between site work and the ledger creates admin drag.</li>
                        </ul>
