                    <p>Transitioning from manual tracking to unstoppable performance.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="infographic-grid">
                    <div class="state-card current">
                        <h3>Current State (Manual & Fragmented)</h3>
                        <ul>
                            <li><strong>Disconnected Data:</strong> Job history is buried in email trails and portal links (Service Channel/Versa).</li>
                            <li><strong>Manual Job Sheets:</strong> Lads have to sign paper/digital PDFs which then need manual processing.</li>
                            <li><strong>Scheduling Guesswork:</strong> Admin teams have to manually optimize routes for 10 lads across the country.</li>
                            <li><strong>Vulnerable PPMs:</strong> Relying on memory or docs to know when a shutter service is due in 6 months.</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div class="state-card future">
                        <h3>Future State (BigChange)</h3>
                        <ul>
                            <li><strong>Single Source of Truth:</strong> Every Starbucks or Motor Fuel site has a complete digital history of every shutter, lock, and door.</li>
                            <li><strong>Professional Digital Cards:</strong> Instant, high-quality job cards with before/after photos and site-specific RAMS.</li>
                            <li><strong>Intelligent Routing:</strong> Route Optimizer cuts fuel spend and travel time for your national coverage.</li>
                            <li><strong>Automated PPMs:</strong> Set the recurrence once, and the system automatically flags the job when it's due.</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
